    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [250ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-tikka-masala-basa-curry-with-almonds-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>flaked almonds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once golden, transfer the <strong>toasted almonds</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-tikka-masala-basa-curry-with-almonds-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and quarter your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways and deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-tikka-masala-basa-curry-with-almonds-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!), then wash your <strong>spinach </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>quartered shallot</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>crushed garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped tomato</strong>,<strong> creamed coconut </strong>and the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add most of your <strong>coriander</strong> (save some leaves for garnish!) with a small handful of <strong>spinach </strong>(save the rest for later!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>green tikka sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-tikka-masala-basa-curry-with-almonds-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat<strong> </strong>with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a little knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>green tikka sauce </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until very fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-tikka-masala-basa-curry-with-almonds-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped fish</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-tikka-masala-basa-curry-with-almonds-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-7 min further or until the fish is cooked through and the sauce has thickened</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once the fish is cooked through, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>spinach </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>green tikka masala fish curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-tikka-masala-basa-curry-with-almonds-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>green tikka masala fish curry </strong>with the<strong> cauliflower rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Top with the <strong>toasted almonds</strong> and <strong>remaining coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
